description: agent-paste shared agent workflow
alwaysApply: true
---

Follow the shared repo protocol. Do not create a Cursor-only workflow.

Cursor Composer 2.5 is the preferred implementation workhorse for ready,
well-scoped Linear issues in this repo. Use it for implementation work while
the queue-moving loop owns review, quality gates, and escalation.

Read these before implementation work:

- `AGENTS.md`
- `docs/agents/workflow.md`
- `docs/agents/repo-navigation.md`
- `docs/agents/skill-usage.md`
- `docs/agents/remote-cursor-agent.md`
- `docs/ops/project-status.md`
- `CONTEXT.md`
- `docs/specs/README.md`
- `docs/adr/README.md`
- the assigned Linear issue and linked docs

Only implement issues that are:

- in Linear team `AP`
- labeled `ready-for-agent`
- labeled `remote-cursor`
- unblocked
- scoped to one PR

Use `agent-paste-implement-issue` for the implementation flow. Before opening a
PR, run or request `agent-paste-local-code-review` on the branch when the
environment supports it. Address blocking findings before PR handoff.

When the queue-moving loop sends `Changes Requested` feedback, continue in the
same thread, branch, and PR. Read the PR review comments, push fixes to the same
PR, and move the issue back to `In Review` when ready.

Stop and comment in Linear when product scope, security posture, credentials,
provider approval, or ADR decisions are missing.
